            <thetext>If you touch inside the list of a qx.Mobile Menu, the &quot;active&quot; state is not displayed by a blue background like on the qx.Mobile List.

This is because the touch event are being prevented by the ScrollComposite. This behavior is wanted, as if it contains a TextArea, the touch events would cause some side effects on touch device like iPad.

We should make this behavior configurable, and disable it by default on qx.Mobile Menu.</thetext>
